      "message": "Line 116: 🟡 Suggestion: `@Volatile` is unnecessary here. Both `ProcessLifecycleOwner` callbacks (`onStart`/`onStop`) and the `idleShutdownRunnable` (posted to main looper Handler) execute on the main thread, so all reads and writes to `isInForeground` are already serialized. The only cross-thread read is in `onPushProcessed()` which checks `isInForeground` — but that just gates whether to schedule the idle shutdown and is tolerant of a stale read. Consider removing `@Volatile` or documenting why cross-thread access is expected.",
