      "side": 1,
      "message": "[critical] Line 77: 🔴 Critical: Same issue as in UnifiedPush path. `app.onMessageReceived(remoteMessage)` dispatches to the daemon executor asynchronously — `pushNotificationReceived` and `processPush` queue work but don\u0027t block until it completes. The `finally` block then releases the WakeLock and calls `onPushProcessed()`, which stops the foreground service via `ACTION_PUSH_DONE`. The daemon may still be processing the push (e.g., ICE negotiation for an incoming call). Without either a WakeLock or a foreground service, the process is vulnerable to being killed by the OOM killer.\n\nAt minimum, defer `onPushProcessed()` until the daemon signals it has finished processing the push notification.",
      "revId": "a4af0f6a6b27fcb737c10471e848f9bb4ef57843",
