      "side": 1,
      "message": "[critical] Line 74: 🔴 Critical: `onPushProcessed()` is called in the `finally` block immediately after `app?.onMessage(msg)` returns. However, `onMessage()` internally dispatches work to the daemon asynchronously (via `pushNotificationReceived` and `processPush`). Calling `onPushProcessed()` here releases the WakeLock AND stops the foreground service (via `ACTION_PUSH_DONE`) before the daemon has finished processing the push message. On low-memory devices this can cause the process to be killed mid-processing, resulting in lost messages.\n\nThe same pattern existed before (30s WakeLock as safety net), but now the WakeLock is released early *and* the foreground service is torn down. You need a completion signal from the daemon processing, or at minimum keep the foreground service alive for the full timeout and only release the WakeLock early.\n\nConsider adding a callback/suspending mechanism so `onPushProcessed()` is only called after `pushNotificationReceived` and `processPush` have completed their work.",
